text: remember the fuss a few months ago when
Apple replaced good old Google Maps with
its own new Maps app the app was pretty
the data not so much Tim Cook apologized
and actually suggested that we use
somebody else's app I recommend using
this one it's the new Google Maps app
for iPhone Google just released this app
based on its own database of the world
the design is clean and modern Street
View lets you see what any address looks
like and compass view lets you look
around someplace without actually being
there everything is built in points of
interest reviews photos even making
reservations and the public
transportation feature is just amazing
everything swipes horizontally show me a
different restaurant show me a different
route show me the next driving direction
and above all I love how good the data
is here's me entering an address on
Apple's Maps 200 West 79th say what on
Google Maps BAM it knows on this being
able to say Siri give me directions to
the airport but I'll love knowing that
Google Maps is going to drive me where I
want to go instead of driving me crazy
